<paragraph blockId="7.[810,1420,160,458]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,972,160,184]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">Identification.</emphasis>
Our male specimen was identified based on the venter of the fore femur without a basal tubercle (
<figureCitation box="[857,942,227,251]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="8.[168,231,1098,1118]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,160,1074]" captionTargetId="figure-63@8.[168,1417,160,1074]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 7. Gerromorpha from eastern Maranhão state, northeastern Brazil. A–C. Tachygerris adamsoni, macropterous female. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Lateral view. D, E. Halobatopsis platensis, apterous female. D. Dorsal view. E. Ventral view. F, G. Merragata hebroides, macropterous male. F. Dorsal view. G. Ventral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="558">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
), but instead with a fringe of setae on this area. The females have the posterior margin of abdominal sternum VII without projections, distinctly shorter than the posterior projection of the last abdominal laterotergite (
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser N" box="[931,1068,361,386]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" pagination="94 - 138" refId="ref10434" refString="Nieser N (1970) Gerridae of Suriname and the Amazon with additional records of other neotropical species. Studies on the fauna of Suriname and other Guyanas 12 (47): 94 - 138." type="journal article" year="1970">Nieser 1970</bibRefCitation>
; Morales-Castaño and Molano- Rendón 2009).
</paragraph>
