<paragraph blockId="7.[810,1420,587,963]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,971,732,756]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">Identification.</emphasis>
Our material was identified based on the males, which bear antennomere I not incrassate, longer than the others; fore femur without anterior tuft of stout setae or ventral row of long stout spines; hind femur straight; and venter of abdominal segments VII– VIII deeply longitudinally grooved (
<bibRefCitation author="Hungerford HB" box="[1203,1392,900,924]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" pagination="529 - 588" refId="ref9585" refString="Hungerford HB (1954) The genus Rheumatobates Bergroth (Hemiptera - Gerridae). University of Kansas Science Bulletin 36 (7): 529 - 588. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 24625" type="journal article" year="1954">Hungerford 1954</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
